            <abstract>
<p>The homily concerns Christ's Nativity. According to the indication in <ref type="mss" corresp="BerOrFol117"/> it is intended for reading
at Christmas (<q xml:lang="gez">በጌና፡</q>). It corresponds to no. 201 in Akhrass' list.</p>
                <p>The same homily is also attested in two excerpts which form part of the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1586Hayman"/>, but this transmission
                    took place independently from that in <ref type="mss" corresp="BerOrFol117"/>, to which the present record refers.</p>
            </abstract>
